sentences.english: The third 'coincidence' stage is not deterministic.
sentences.chinese: 第三個“相合”的階段是不確定的。

sentences.english: The right part of the word can be considered as "zhou".
sentences.chinese: 左右兩旁相合，可以推測這個字就是“祲”字。

sentences.english: Well, at first, of course they help each other out.
sentences.chinese: 這個嘛，當然一開始會互相合作咯。

sentences.english: And to this agree the words of the prophets; as it is written
sentences.chinese: 衆先知的話，也與這意思相合。

sentences.english: What agreement does Christ have with Beliar?
sentences.chinese: 基督和彼列有什麼相合呢？

sentences.english: He also directed federal agencies to cooperate with each other.
sentences.chinese: 他還要求聯邦各機構互相合作。

sentences.english: What, with the largest portion of your mind -- sentiments -- tastes?
sentences.chinese: 我們想法一致，觀點相合，總之大家意氣相投。

sentences.english: My family members are cooperative with one another.
sentences.chinese: 我的家庭成員之間互相合作。

sentences.english: They could cooperation with each other to learning.
sentences.chinese: 他們可以互相合作學習。

sentences.english: We want regulators to work cooperatively but not be captured by those they monitor.
sentences.chinese: 我們希望監管者互相合作但是又不會被上司逮個正着。

sentences.english: To measure the consistancy of semi-solid and solid bituminous mixtures.
sentences.chinese: 要測量半固體和固體瀝青混合料的相合性。

sentences.english: Yet even then their testimony did not agree.
sentences.chinese: 他們就這樣作見證，也是各不相合。

sentences.english: The suspicion of Procris is always harmful to cooperative work.
sentences.chinese: 在互相合作中，胡亂猜疑往往是有害的。

sentences.english: Difference between the social systems shall not be an obstacle to their cooperation.
sentences.chinese: 社會制度的不同，不應妨礙互相合作。

sentences.english: Participants collaborated to act as a building or community facility.
sentences.chinese: 同學互相合作，以身體扮演指定的社區設施或建築。

sentences.english: Under the general condition, the consistency of the ridge estimation is proved.
sentences.chinese: 在一定條件下證明了此嶺估計的相合性。
